			    STPJS 199</div>
  <p class="cont">cannot obtain the blessings by pursuing any other course except the way marked out by the Lord.
  What if we should attempt to get the gift of the Holy Ghost through any other means<span class="footRef">1</span> except the
  signs or way which God hath appointed&mdash;would we obtain it? Certainly not; all other means
  would fail. The Lord says do so and so, and I will bless you.</p>
  <div class="topic">Key Words of the Priesthood</div>
  <p class="std">There are certain key words<span class="footRef">2</span> and signs<span class="footRef">3</span> belonging to the Priesthood which must be observed
  in order to obtain the blessing.<span class="footRef">4</span> The sign of Peter was to repent and be baptized for the remission
  of sins, with the promise of the gift of the Holy Ghost;<span class="footRef">5</span> and in no other way is the gift of the Holy
  Ghost obtained.<span class="footRef">6</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Difference Between the Holy Ghost and the Gift of the Holy Ghost</div>
  <p class="std">There is a difference between the Holy Ghost and the gift of the Holy Ghost. Cornelius<span class="footRef">7</span>
  received the Holy Ghost before he was baptized, which was the convincing power of God<span class="footRef">8</span> unto him
  of the truth of the Gospel,<span class="footRef">9</span> but he could not receive the gift of the Holy Ghost until after he was
  baptized. Had he not taken this sign or ordinance upon him, the Holy Ghost which convinced him
  of the truth of God,<span class="footRef">10</span> would have left him. Until he obeyed these ordinances and received the gift
  of the Holy Ghost,<span class="footRef">11</span> by the laying on of hands,<span class="footRef">12</span> according to the order of God,<span class="footRef">13</span> he could not have
  healed the sick or commanded an evil spirit to come out of a man, and it obey him; for the spirits
  might say unto him, as they did to the sons of Sceva: &ldquo;Paul we know and Jesus we know, but who
  are ye?&rdquo;<span class="footRef">14</span> It mattereth not whether we live long or short<span class="footRef">15</span> on the earth after we come to a knowledge
  of these principles and obey them unto the end.<span class="footRef">16</span> I know that all men will be damned if they do not
  come in the way<span class="footRef">17</span> which He hath opened, and this is the way marked out by the word of the Lord.<span class="footRef">18</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The Universal Resurrection</div>
  <p class="std">As concerning the resurrection, I will merely say that all men will come from the grave as they
  lie down, whether old or young; there will not be &ldquo;added unto their stature one cubit,&rdquo;<span class="footRef">19</span> neither taken
  from it; all will be raised by the power of God,<span class="footRef">20</span></p>
